Semi-Annual Monitoring Checklist

INSTRUCTIONS: This form is to be completed during semi-annual clinical monitoring visits through interviews with the facility manager and staff in the FP and CAC units, as well as through structured observation and record review.
Facility details  
Date of clinical monitoring visit  
Visiting team members (name and organization)  
Types of support provided by ABRI III (tick all that apply) CC and CAC support
PM (FS NSV)
PPUID
Service integration
Youth friendly services
Community referral linkages
Others, specify
Routine service provision
Question Response options
Which of the following FP services are available today or upon request any day that this health facility is open? (Tick all that apply) IUD
Jadelle or Sino-Implant
Implanon
Contraceptive pills
Injectables (DMPA)
Male condoms
Female condoms
Male Sterilization
Female Sterilization
Safe abortion related services are available today (or up on request ant time that the health facility is open)? (Tick all that apply) MVA Abortion
MA Abortion
EC/DC Abortion
MVA Post-abortion
MA Post-abortion
EC/DC Post-abortion
Post abortion related services are available today (or up on request ant time that the health facility is open)? (Tick all that apply) MVA Abortion
MA Abortion
EC/DC Abortion
MVA Post-abortion
MA Post-abortion
EC/DC Post-abortion
Which of the following post-abortion FP methods are provided in the CAC unit itself (i.e. without need for internal referral)? (Tick all that apply) IUD
Jadelle or Sino-Implant
Implanon
Contraceptive pills
Injectables (DMPA)
Male condoms
Female condoms
Other (specify)
Which of the following post-abortion FP methods are provided to CAC clients through internal referrals to the FP unit? (Tick all that apply) IUD
Jadelle or Sino-Implant
Implanon
Contraceptive pills
Injectables (DMPA)
Male condoms
Female condoms
Other (specify)
For which FP methods or services not available at this facility, and are clients referred to other facility? (Tick all that apply) IUD
Jadelle or Sino-Implant
Implanon
Contraceptive pills
Injectables (DMPA)
Male condoms
Female condoms
Other (specify)
Community referrals and qualified staffing
Question Response options
Does this facility receive FP referrals from community health workers in the catchment area? (Verify by observing whether there are confirmed referral slips dated within the past two months)
How many providers currently posted to the FP unit have been trained and certified as competent in the provision of comprehensive contraception (CC)? (Verify through review of records of staff who have been trained and certified as competent and who are currently posted to the FP unit)
How many providers currently posted to the CAC unit have been certified as competent in the provision of comprehensive abortion care (CAC) (Verify through review of records of staff who have been trained and certified as competent and who are currently posted to the CAC unit)
How many providers currently posted in the CAC unit have been trained and certified as competent in both CAC and CC (Verify through review of records of staff who have been trained and certified as competent and who are currently posted to the CAC unit)
How many provider teams in the health facility have been trained and certified as competent in the provision of PMs (Provider team defined as a physician and nurse or health officer and nurse).
How many providers currently posted to the maternity/delivery ward been trained and certified as competent in postpartum IUD insertion?
How many providers currently posted to the FP and CAC unit been trained in youth-friendly services in addition to CC or CAC services?
Stock out and logistics
Question Response options
During the past two months, has the facility experienced stock out of any of the following commodities? (Tick all that apply) UID (Copper T or LNG)
Jadelle or Sino-Implant
Implanon
Contraceptive pills
Injectables (DMPA)
Male condoms
Female condoms
Are the most recent FP and CAC commodity requests correctly based on previous consumption and stock at hand (Verify through review of most recent RRF)  
Did most recent delivery of FP and CAC commodities match the request made through the RRF? (Verify through review of most recent RRF)  
Have staff in the FP, CAC and pharmacy units been oriented on use of the IPLS for requesting and management of FP and CAC commodities? (Verify through interview with department heads or facility in-charge)  
Infrastructure
Question Response options
Do counseling rooms in FP and CAC service units ensure client privacy and confidentiality? (Verify through observation)
Do procedure rooms in FP and CAC service units ensure client privacy and confidentiality? (Verify through observation)
Do FP and CAC procedure rooms have adequate lighting for the performance of all procedures (including PM services where applicable)? (Verify through observation)
Infection prevention
Question Response options
Are Infection prevention protocol charts posted in both FP and CAC service units? (Verify through observation)
Is there a functioning set-up for decontamination in both FP and CAC service units? (Verify through observation)
Is there a sterilization/HLD mechanism in place, such as sterilizer, boiler, autoclave in both FP and CAC service units or available to them in a central sterilization unit in the facility? (Verify through observation)
Are there leak-proof and puncture-proof containers in both FP and CAC service units? (Verify through observation)
IVDM / FP compliance
Question Response options
Are clients offered information on range of methods A copy of the Tiahrt poster (method chart) or a flipchart on all FP methods available in the FP and CAC service units? (Verify through observation)
Are there any targets or quotas for service providers in the FP or CAC unit for serving a certain number of FP clients or for the provision of certain FP methods? (Verify through interview with department heads or in-charge)
Are there incentives for staff in the FP or CAC service units to provide a certain FP method or incentives for clients in these units to adopt a certain FP method? (Verify through interview with department heads or in-charge)
Are there signed consent forms for all PM and CAC procedures conducted during the past two months (Verify through review of signed consent forms against procedures performed during past 2 months)
Management and supervision
Question Response options
Are national guidelines and standards for FP and CAC service provision available in each unit?
Have staff in the FP and CAC units received a facilitative supervision visit from on-site / off-site supervisor or ABRI project staff during the past six (6) months (Verify through review of dated supervision report at facility that specifies problems discussed action steps recommended)
Is this facility part of health care finance (HCF) board scheme? if so; does the facility use part of the revenue generated for FP/CAC related services?
Do FP and CAC service units have dedicated hours or space for youth clients (Verify through observation)
OOC and instruments
Question Response options
If COPE has been introduced at the facility, have the staff conducted a COPE exercise during the past quarter?
How many IUD KITS (functional and in good condition) are available? (Verify through observation)
How many IUD REMOVAL KITS (functional and in good condition) are available? (Verify through observation)
How many IMPLANT INSERTION KITS (functional and in good condition) are available? (Verify through observation)
How many IMPLANT REMOVAL KITS (functional and in good condition) are available? (Verify through observation)
How many MVA KITS (functional and in good condition) are available? (Verify through observation)
How many MINILAPAROTOMY KITS (functional and in good condition) are available? (Verify through observation)
How many NSV KITS (functional and in good condition) are available? (Verify through observation)
